Engineering News editor Terence Creamer discusses the National Energy Crisis Committee's planned initiatives for dealing with the country's electricity crisis; the proposed declaration of the energy crisis as a State of Disaster; Eskom's Generation Recovery Plan and the focus on getting units at the Kusile power station in operation again; what President Cyril Ramaphosa might outline in his State of the Nation next week; and if a State of Disaster will help the country overcome the electricity crisis.